reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Eh, Just alright
reviews.reviewText: These are definitely not worth the price of $89-$99. They are not bone conducting and the sound quality is less than stellar. However, if you need a set of ear buds that allow you to hear what’s going on around you and you don’t mind the tinny sound they will work. I paid $14 after coupons and discount codes for these and that’s about all that they are worth. They are not bone conducting. My AirPods are definitely better by 1,000,000% but I don’t have to worry about losing one at the gym with these. The case is very cheap feeling. I’m sure it will break soon. Definitely do not pay more than $15 for these.
